description: This 1961 Ford Ranchero is a vehicle that you don't see alot of anymore. This one is still original. It has the 170 CI 6 cylinder engine with the original 3 speed on the column transmission. This one came red from the factory with red and white vinyl interior and it still has both colors now. It has been repainted and re-upholstered I am sure but back to original colors. The paint is driver quality but shows good. It has a few small scratches but nothing bad. It also has a few bubbles mostly around the trim but again not bad. Both the front and back bumpers looks good. They don't appear to be that old. It has a nice button on bed cover and the bed itself under the cover is in really good condition. All the exterior lights work as does the interior dome light. The seat, door panels and headliner all look good as does the rubber floor mat. The speedometer works and so do the wipers. Both door glass rolls up and down good. It has a Grant steering wheel on it now. The tires are 185/75R13 and have good tread on them. There is some rust underneath the car.( See pics) The passenger side floor pan was replaced and a good job was done. The engine runs good and the transmission shifts good. It is no show car by any means but is a nice quality driver.
title: 1961 Ford Ranchero
